What you need to know:

On Saturday, Kenya edged out Japan 31-14 to finish third during the first leg of the Emirates Invitational Sevens where Argentina claimed their third win on the trot, beating France 19-7 in the finalKenya opens their quest against Uganda in their Pool “Blue” at 11.09am on Friday before meeting Canada at 3.14pmAt the same time, Kenya Lionesses coach Felix Oloo said the second leg of the Emirates Invitational Sevens will give them another opportunity to improve after they failed to win a match in the first leg